**Files:** `src/components/notifications/NotificationSheet.tsx`, `src/pages/CreviaStudio.tsx`, `src/components/studio/workspaces/StudioWorkspacesHub.tsx`

**Problem 1 — "🔒 Encrypted message" body:**
The DB trigger correctly stores this text for E2EE messages (can't change without a migration). Fix in UI only:
- In `NotificationSheet.tsx`, add a helper: if `n.type === 'message'` and `n.body === '🔒 Encrypted message'`, replace the displayed body with `"Tap to open conversation"` in muted style

**Problem 2 — Navigate to specific chat room:**
The `notification.data.room_id` already contains the room ID. Wire it up:
1. In `NotificationSheet.tsx` → `handleClick`: for `type === 'message'`, build URL: `` `/crevia-studio?tab=chat&roomId=${n.data?.room_id}` `` instead of the static nav string
2. In `CreviaStudio.tsx`: read `searchParams.get("roomId")` and pass it as `initialRoomId` prop to `<StudioWorkspacesHub initialRoomId={activeRoomId} />`
